Introductory formalities الآجُرُّوم - a berber word meaning الفقر الصوفي from a town called صنهاحة - Moroccan passes away 728 (AH) Speech الكَلاَمُ (٢) هُوَ اللَّفْظُ المُرَكَّبُ المُفِيدُ بِالوَضْعِ
Speech according to the grammarians consists of these 4 things. - إصطلحي.
لفظ excludes things like إشارات 1 (gestures), writings, or signs (like traffic lights) مركب excludes singluar words مفيد excludes phrases that give no benefit (can the speaker stop after the speech has ended such that the one who is addressed is not waiting for more information?) 2 Speech linguistically can be gestures: فأشارت إليه قالوا كيف نكلم من كان في المهد صبيّا, or diagrams or signs. Not necessarily uttered&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
&ldquo;If zayd&rdquo;. This sentence has more than one word, but is not مفيد&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
